<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About StoryLoom</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>

    {{> header}}

    <main class="container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h1>About StoryLoom</h1>
            
            <p>StoryLoom is an online digital archive for folklore and mythological texts.</p>
            
            <p>This platform was developed as an undergraduate project to centralize, preserve, and share global tales, taking inspiration from long-standing digital preservation efforts.</p>
            
            <p>The entire StoryLoom collection is yours to explore and enjoy.</p>
            
            <p>All StoryLoom texts are completely free and always will be.</p>
            
            <h2>StoryLoom Mission Statement</h2>
            <p><em>To encourage the preservation and distribution of global folklore.</em></p>
            
            <h2>More about StoryLoom</h2>
            <p>To read more about StoryLoom, choose one of these topics:</p>
            
            <ul class="dashed-list">
                <li><a href="#">Background, History and Philosophy</a>: Various essays and articles regarding the archive.</li>
                <li><a href="/faq">Help and how-to</a>: Guides on navigating and reading the texts.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </main>

    {{> footer}}

</body>
</html>